5:
Sigh... You're not going to listen to
me, are you?
8: Save your excuses for the jailhouse!
11: No, I don't think I will.
14:
Hey, did you see a woman run by
here?
17:
Um... I cannot say for certain. I might
have seen someone run off that
way...
28:
Phew! Thank you very much. You
saved me from a whole heap of
trouble.
31:
Now... Would you mind telling us
more about your predicament? I
believe I've seen your face on a
wanted poster.
35:
If I recall correctly, the name listed
was... Giselle. You're wanted for
suspected smuggling of those
accursed weapons from the
Kaleidoscope.
39:
You knew all that and still chose to
help me?
44:
I merely thought we should hear
your side before we decide whether
to turn you in or not. Now, could you
tell us your story?
53:
So in other words, it's all a
misunderstanding?
57:
I have no idea why anyone would
accuse me of such a thing...
Although I do have a guess.
61:
You see, I actually collect cryptic
artifacts from the Kaleidoscope,
including those "accursed weapons"
you spoke of.
64:
But I would never smuggle them. 
It took a lot of work to get them, so
why in the world would I give them
away?
69:
...Do you have any proof to support
your claim?
77:
But there's also no proof that you've
been smuggling, right?
79:
In that case, why not just ask the
Guild Knights for help?
83:
The Guild Knights are the ones who
made those posters in the first
place. Why would I go to the people
who suspect me of—
87:
I understand your reservations, but if
you speak the truth, you have
nothing to fear.
89:
And even if you don't, the Guild
Knights cannot touch you without
evidence.
93:
I am Finn, commander of the Guild
Knights' central task force here in
Palpebra.
96:
I'll cut straight to the point. You're
free to go.
105:
Nothing in your statement
contradicted what we've collected
on our end. We also haven't found
any evidence that supports the
accusations against you.
108:
In other words, due to lack of
evidence, we cannot detain you.
118:
I cannot dismiss the accusations
against you either. Especially since it
seems you've been neglecting to
report your cryptic artifacts to the
Guild.
127:
Considering how many times you
have "forgotten," as well as the
scope, it would be very easy to
misinterpret your actions as illegal.
Be sure to file the correct papers
immediately.
135:
Now, this is merely my own
speculations, but... If you are
innocent, it may be best to avoid
going home for a while.
139:
Do you think... the true culprit lives
near me?
143:
I do. Someone would have to know
you very well to lure you into such a
predicament.
144:
I'd like to place you under
surveillance, but...
148:
In that case, why don't you stay with
us, Giselle?
157:
Not at all! We've got plenty of rooms
available. You'd be surprised how
big the place is. Heck, even we don't
know!
162:
Oh my, it sounds like quite the
estate! That should work quite nicely!
166:
Excellent! We managed to fit
everything in three rooms!
171: Um... Are all of these cryptic artifacts?
177:
Just look at this beautiful form! You
can tell this is from a culture far
outside the lands of Palpebra, or
even the Farlands for that matter!
180:
And this one! Despite its equally
elegant form, the power it holds is
middling at best. One can't help but
wonder why such a thing was made—
184:
Ah, my apologies. I just get so
excited when dealing with cryptic
artifacts.
188:
No wonder you were suspected of
smuggling...
192:
But the true culprit remains at large.
Your absence has no doubt shaken
them...
196:
I'm sure it has. I will find the true
smuggler and pay them back
tenfold.
200:
Especially since they are the reason
I now have so much paperwork to
do!
